# AI-Powered Autonomous Mobile Robot for Poultry Farm Waste Management

## Overview

Poultry farms generate a large amount of organic waste that requires frequent cleaning to maintain hygiene, reduce odor, and improve overall farm productivity. Manual waste handling is labor-intensive and exposes workers to potential health risks.

This project explores the development of an AI-powered autonomous mobile robot designed to assist in poultry farm waste management. The system integrates robotic mobility, sensing, and intelligent decision-making to automate waste detection and collection tasks within indoor poultry farm environments.

---

## Objectives

* Design an autonomous mobile robot platform suitable for poultry farm environments
* Implement AI-based detection or classification of poultry waste
* Develop navigation capabilities for structured farm layouts
* Demonstrate automated waste collection and farm sanitation assistance

---

## System Architecture

Robot Platform:

* Mobile robotic base

Computation:

* Onboard processing unit for AI inference and robot control

Sensors:

* Camera for visual detection
* Additional sensors for navigation and obstacle avoidance

Software Stack:

* Robot Operating System (ROS)
* Computer vision / AI model for waste detection
* Autonomous navigation algorithms

---

## Key Features

* Autonomous navigation in indoor farm environments
* AI-based waste detection using camera input
* Mobile robotic platform for sanitation tasks
* Integration of perception, navigation, and robotic control

---

## Implementation

The robot operates through the following workflow:

1. Environmental perception through onboard cameras
2. AI model processes visual input to detect poultry waste
3. Navigation system guides the robot toward target locations
4. Waste collection or cleaning mechanism performs sanitation tasks

The system integrates perception, decision-making, and robotic control into a unified automation workflow.

---

## Results

The prototype demonstrates the feasibility of using autonomous mobile robots to assist in poultry farm waste management.

Testing was conducted in a simulated or controlled environment to evaluate navigation performance, detection accuracy, and system integration.

The results highlight the potential of robotics and AI to improve efficiency and hygiene in agricultural operations.

